 ## Allowlist
@@ -97,6 +98,23 @@ The old recovery prose was "remove the marker, then re-run `hive run`". That wor
 - **No audit trail.** Hand-edits don't land on the `hive/state` branch; future `hive metrics` walks miss the recovery action entirely.
 - **No JSON envelope.** `hive markers clear --json` is part of the same agent-callable surface as `hive approve --json` and `hive run --json`.
 
+## Review stop-hook guard
+
+The historical review-fix stop-hook failure shape is:
+
+```text
+REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=fix_failed message="claude stop hook did not signal completion"
+```
+
+Do not clear this marker blindly. The daemon healer first re-evaluates `claude-exit-status.json`, review artifacts, worktree status, and commit/no-change evidence; if proof is sufficient it emits `claude_completion_fallback` and reruns review. If manual recovery is needed, guard the clear with the observed pass:
+
+```bash
+hive markers clear <task-folder> --name REVIEW_ERROR --match-attr phase=fix,reason=fix_failed,pass=<N>
+hive run <task-folder>
+```
+
+Use that template for already-parked tasks 58 / PR #622, 287 / PR #623, and 288 / PR #624 only after substituting the concrete folder/pass and confirming the marker attrs still match.
+
