+date: 2026-07-11
+slug: review-fallback-proof-hardening
+pages: [stages/review, modules/daemon]
+---
+
+Hardened the 6-review Claude stop-hook completion fallback after review found
+three proof gaps and one healer pass-advance gap.
+
+`lib/hive/stages/review.rb` now treats `completion_evidence["exit_code"]` as
+strict evidence: missing or non-numeric values no longer coerce to zero. The
+missing-output blocker also recognizes the existing
+`tmux_session_terminated before writing expected output file` reviewer error
+shape, not only the older `expected output file missing` / `missing output`
+phrases. No-change proof from the final message now requires a standalone
+`HIVE_FIX_NO_CHANGE: ...` line, so the inline prompt example in
+`templates/fix_prompt.md.erb` cannot satisfy the fallback verifier.
+
+`lib/hive/daemon/stale_agent_healer.rb` now writes the normal
+`reviews/fix-success-NN.md` sentinel after proof-positive stop-hook recovery
+and before requeueing `hive run`, so `next_pass_for` advances past the
+completed fix pass instead of classifying it as `:fix_incomplete`.
+
+Focused validation passed without Bundler because the locked gems are not
+installed locally: `ruby -Itest test/unit/stages/review/run_reviewers_test.rb`,
+`ruby -Itest test/unit/daemon/stale_agent_healer_test.rb`, and
+`ruby -Itest test/integration/run_review_test.rb`. The equivalent
+`bundle exec ruby ...` invocations failed before test startup with
+`Bundler::GemNotFound`.
+
+Updated [[stages/review]] and [[modules/daemon]]. Page count unchanged, so
+[[index]] did not need a catalog update. Did not edit compiled [[log]].
