+pages: [stages/review, modules/protected_files, state-model]
+---
+
+Hardened the second pass of 6-review Claude stop-hook fallback proof.
+
+`reviews/fix-no-change-NN.md` is now treated as orchestrator-owned fallback
+evidence: it is excluded from reviewer-file classification and included in
+the fix-agent protected snapshot, so a fix agent cannot create a no-change
+proof file to satisfy fallback completion after a missing Stop-hook sentinel.
+
+The fallback verifier now re-parses the current reviewer/escalation artifacts
+after the fix spawn and requires accepted finding evidence to still be present,
+instead of trusting the pre-spawn accepted-findings payload. Truncated or
+corrupted current artifacts therefore reject fallback completion instead of
+allowing a stale payload to write `reviews/fix-success-NN.md`.
+
+`Hive::ClaudeLauncher.record_claude_pid` now keeps polling for the wrapper's
+`claude-child.pid` artifact until the configured PID wait deadline, retaining
+the tmux pane PID only as a fallback if the child artifact never appears.
+
+Updated [[stages/review]], [[modules/protected_files]], and [[state-model]].
+Page count unchanged, so [[index]] did not need a catalog update. Did not edit
+compiled [[log]].
