+## Claude tmux stop-hook recovery
+
+For affected Claude Code versions, keep `claude.mode: headless` as the safe workaround when operators see review-fix rows stuck on `REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=fix_failed message="claude stop hook did not signal completion"`. Hive does not auto-revert that config. Tmux mode is accepted only when Hive can prove the fix agent exited 0 from `claude-exit-status.json`, parse the review artifacts, verify the worktree, and find commit or explicit no-change evidence.
+
+Accepted proof emits `claude_completion_fallback` at WARN level in `<task>/events.jsonl` and updates `<task>/status.md`. Inspect it with:
+
+```bash
+grep claude_completion_fallback <task-folder>/events.jsonl
+tail -40 <task-folder>/status.md
+```
+
+If a parked task cannot be auto-proven, use guarded manual recovery only after inspecting the marker and artifacts:
+
+```bash
+hive markers clear <task-folder> --name REVIEW_ERROR --match-attr phase=fix,reason=fix_failed,pass=<N>
+hive run <task-folder>
+```
+
+For the known stuck rows 58 / PR #622, 287 / PR #623, and 288 / PR #624, substitute each concrete folder and pass. Do not clear if the marker attrs have changed or if the expected proof/audit trail is absent.
